Definition.WordDefinition:
Compute \Com*pute"\ (k[o^]m*p[=u]t"), v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Computed}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Computing}.] [L. computare. See {Count}, v. t.] To determine by calculation; to reckon; to count. [1913 Webster]
Two days, as we compute the days of heaven. --Milton. [1913 Webster]
What's done we partly may compute, But know not what's resisted. --Burns.
Syn: To calculate; number; count; reckon; estimate; enumerate; rate. See {Calculate}. [1913 Webster]

computing n 1: the branch of engineering science that studies (with the aid of computers) computable processes and structures [syn: {computer science}] 2: the procedure of calculating; determining something by mathematical or logical methods [syn: {calculation}, {computation}]
